 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Senior Talent Acquisition Specialist Kitware Remote Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Kitware is hiring a Senior Talent Acquisition Specialist to help us further our mission of having a positive impact on the world through open science! This role is responsible for the full cycle talent acquisition strategy and processes to support the company’s growth initiatives, including effective and efficient recruitment of roles across technical and administrative positions. 
 
 
In this position you will: 
Collaborate with hiring managers and others involved in the recruitment process to manage talent acquisition and candidate pipelines to meet company staffing goals 
Partner with technical and administrative teams to promote Kitware’s value proposition to potential candidates and communicate our Mission, Values, and Why 
Develop and advertise job postings to create applicant pools and talent pipelines 
Manage the interview and selection processes, including testing and screening resources, and interviewer training 
Conduct initial resume reviews and phone screens, and make recommendations for moving candidates through the interview and selection process 
Develop and maintain partnerships with external entities such as ATS vendors, recruitment agencies, universities, and recruitment professional organizations 
Work on integration of diversity and inclusion initiatives into the talent acquisition process 
Conduct passive candidate searches and outreach to develop candidate leads 
Attend college/university career fairs 
Develop and manage internal talent acquisition metrics and analytics processes, benchmarking, and monthly reporting 
Work with management to refine and update overall talent acquisition strategies 
 Required Qualifications: 
Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Business Management, or a related field, and 8+ years of relevant experience recruiting for technical and professional level positions, or equivalent combination of education and experience 
Experience using social media platforms to source passive candidates 
Proficiency with Google office products and/or Microsoft Office suite 
Experience with using and managing Applicant Tracking Systems 
In-depth knowledge of talent acquisition and candidate selection best practices 
Excellent organizational and time management skills 
Experience with and understanding of recruitment-related laws and regulations 
Ability to establish and maintain productive working relationships and effective communication with internal and external collaborators 
 Preferred Qualifications: 
Experience recruitment for high-level software engineering, research and development positions in the technology industry, or similar hard-to-fill niche roles 
Experience recruiting for federal government contractor organizations 
Working knowledge of immigration and work visa regulations 
 Company Description 
Kitware collaborates with customers to solve the world’s most complex scientific challenges through customized software solutions. Kitware delivers innovation by focusing on advanced technical computing and state-of-the-art artificial intelligence. Since its founding in 1998, Kitware has developed a reputation for deep technical expertise, honest interactions, and open innovation. We are proud to be a 100% employee-owned company, and honored to be recognized as a Great Place To Work For additional information, please visit kitware.com. You can also follow us on Twitter, LinkedIn, and Facebook. 
 
Additional information 
Kitware is proud to be a 100% employee-owned company . Our team members enjoy a small company environment, flexibility in work assignments, and high levels of independence and responsibility. Besides a great work environment, our comprehensive benefits package includes a generous compensation plan, tuition reimbursement program, flexible working hours, six weeks paid time off, 401(k), health insurance, life insurance, short- and long-term disability insurance, bonus plan, and free coffee, drinks and snacks. 
 
